cs.DL, cs.CR, cs.IR, cs.DB, cs.SE 

This paper discusses the problem of making digital artifacts on the Web verifiable and reliable, which is related to digital libraries (cs.DL), cryptography and security (cs.CR), information retrieval (cs.IR), databases (cs.DB), and software engineering (cs.SE). The proposed solution involves the use of trusty URIs containing cryptographic hash values, which is a technique that can be applied to various types of digital artifacts, including datasets, code, texts, and images. Therefore, this paper could fit into multiple arXiv CS sub-categories, but the ones listed above are the most likely based on the content of the paper.
